To welcome guests into Google’s BrandLab space, the team at Uncorked Studios built a 22-foot-long interactive wall to be an integral part of the workshop experience. The wall sets the stage for the curriculum that is about to come—it brings together the digital and physical worlds by creating a customized experience that contrasts the guests’ data with that of the audience they’re learning about that day, all while the wall is changing modes to facilitate the journey.
